{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/tiredness-fatigue-in-adults/background-information/prevalence/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"127b3983-553b-546e-8f62-ab5da77e7988","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 5c399d44-27e1-49a8-baab-63af4c05875d --><h2>How common is it?</h2><!-- end field 5c399d44-27e1-49a8-baab-63af4c05875d -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 197f0416-4d18-4180-9156-dd45b332f009 --><!-- begin field 00dbddf7-2be1-419c-8a59-1b0f5611b686 --><p><strong>The reported prevalence of tiredness/fatigue varies according to case definitions, methods of assessment, and study settings </strong>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/tiredness-fatigue-in-adults/references/\">Stadje, 2016</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/tiredness-fatigue-in-adults/references/\">Larun, 2019</a>]<strong>.</strong></p><ul><li>Tiredness is one of the most frequent presenting complaints in primary care [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/tiredness-fatigue-in-adults/references/\">Stadje, 2016</a>].</li><li>In a UK community-based postal survey sent to an age- and sex-stratified random sample of 2474 adults from 20 GP practices, 50% of people with chronic disease reported feeling tired/run down as a symptom, and it was the most commonly reported symptom out of 25 possible symptoms [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/tiredness-fatigue-in-adults/references/\">McAteer, 2011</a>].</li><li>In a UK population-based postal survey (n = 15,283 adults), 10–18% of people self-reported current tiredness/fatigue that had lasted 1 month or longer [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/tiredness-fatigue-in-adults/references/\">Pawlikowska, 1994</a>].<ul><li>It is noted, however, that the methodology of asking people directly about tiredness may lead to high self-reported rates.</li></ul></li><li>A UK general practice database study (1990–2001) found that the annual incidence of new tiredness/fatigue was 1.5% [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/tiredness-fatigue-in-adults/references/\">Gallagher, 2004</a>].</li><li>A Swiss population-based cross-sectional survey (n = 2848) found the prevalence of fatigue was 21.9% in the general population [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/tiredness-fatigue-in-adults/references/\">Galland-Decker, 2019</a>].</li><li>A Canadian comparative study of primary care records (n = 103 fatigue symptom and non-fatigue symptom patients) found the period prevalence of presentation with fatigue was 8.2% over a 1-year follow-up period [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/tiredness-fatigue-in-adults/references/\">Nicholson, 2015</a>].</li></ul><p><strong>There are varying reported prevalence rates of chronic fatigue syndrome (CFS) in the literature.</strong></p><ul><li>The prevalence of CFS in community-based studies is low. A meta-analysis of 14 studies found the pooled prevalence for self-reported CFS was 3.28%, and the prevalence following clinical assessment was 0.76%. High variability was observed among self-reported estimates [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/tiredness-fatigue-in-adults/references/\">Johnston, 2013</a>].</li><li>A large primary care cross-sectional study in England (n = 143,000 adults) found the estimated CFS prevalence rate was 0.2%, and overall estimated annual incidence was 0.015% [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/tiredness-fatigue-in-adults/references/\">Nacul, 2011</a>].</li><li>A UK primary care database study of the incidence of CFS and fibromyalgia found the overall annual incidence of recorded cases of CFS was 14.8 per 100,000 people, and the annual incidence rates for CFS diagnoses decreased from 17.5 in 2001 to 12.6 in 2013. The overall annual incidence of recorded fatigue symptoms was 2246 per 100,000 people [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/tiredness-fatigue-in-adults/references/\">Collin, 2017</a>].</li><li>In a cross-sectional study in Poland of people presenting with self-reported fatigue (n = 1400), 4.9% were confirmed as having CFS [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/tiredness-fatigue-in-adults/references/\">Slomko, 2019</a>].</li></ul><!-- end field 00dbddf7-2be1-419c-8a59-1b0f5611b686 --><!-- end item 197f0416-4d18-4180-9156-dd45b332f009 -->","topic":{"id":"61f35df8-36d2-541e-b997-0b78bad96289","topicId":"21fb5f0f-1e06-43c8-990f-bcded8cfc676","topicName":"Tiredness/fatigue in adults","slug":"tiredness-fatigue-in-adults","lastRevised":"Last revised in March 2020","chapters":[{"id":"404cb5e0-c0b1-516d-b548-9486e82f51b3","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"defb4b1a-b1c0-5607-98c7-67099c37b768","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"630ed210-1441-537d-a2e4-80c614c19753","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"4af39332-0dc0-5737-9443-75ab1ccb7e46","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"499e2dc9-675d-5c9c-8e90-33be13310544","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"6d9550cf-4496-5399-9386-2221acab329e","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"124b7023-365f-54a7-a251-a963db2de643","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"fdfc586d-81b1-5d44-a036-a438634061a5","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"56625d11-efe9-5e3f-b417-bc52a5fd8647","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"709f0c15-0a45-522f-ad1f-264575775c32","slug"